</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="67.[2009,2605,513,943]" lastBlockId="67.[1395,2605,955,2602]" pageId="67" pageNumber="125">
Widely used specific name neocaledonica has been changed for gender agreement. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trouessart" authorityYear="1908" box="[2114,2448,831,864]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Notopteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="125" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neocaledonicus">Notopteris neocaledonicus</taxonomicName>
has been described as subspecies of N. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. E. Gray" authorityYear="1859" box="[2440,2597,871,904]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Notopteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="125" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macdonaldii">macdonaldii</taxonomicName>
, but the two are considered distinct based on size. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
